parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical shorts, leading to loss of power, accidents, and injuries. It can also cause malfunctioning of essential systems such as headlights, turn signals, and air conditioning, which can compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The ignition switch fails to turn on
the lights fail to come on
the front lights and turn signals malfunction
the power windows and windshield wipers do not work
the air conditioner does not work
the vehicle stalls
and the headlights suddenly go out during nighttime driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake and Seat Occupant Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake and seat occupant control module can cause the parking brake, warning brake, and airbag warning gauges to illuminate simultaneously, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The parking brake
warning brake
and airbag warning gauges illuminate simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Over-tightened or frozen steering components can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Difficulty steering
stiff or hard steering
unusual noises while steering
loose or detached steering components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear or Failure of Tie Rod Ends (Camber Links)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear or failure of tie rod ends can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Unusual noises while steering
loose or detached steering components
uneven tire wear
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
the engine RPMs surge or redline
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when shifting into neutral or braking.
